From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] mesa.bbappend: leading space + add libclc for panfrost

Mesa 26's PACKAGECONFIG list ends in "gbm" (when DISTRO_FEATURES contains
opengl). The previous append "lima panfrost" had no leading space, so
the resulting string contained "gbmlima panfrost" - bitbake's
invalid-packageconfig QA then rejected the unknown "gbmlima" token.

Add the leading space, and add libclc so the panfrost gallium driver
gets enabled (mesa.inc gates panfrost on "panfrost libclc" being present
together for build-time mesa-clc shader compilation). libclc adds only
build-time DEPENDS (mesa-tools-native) - no runtime cost.

Do NOT add gallium-llvm: that pulls llvmpipe (CPU rasterization) into
GALLIUMDRIVERS and makes libgallium link against shared libLLVM at
runtime, adding ~110 MB to the image. Hardware GPUs like Mali-G31 have
no use for llvmpipe.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
---
diff --git a/recipes-graphics/mesa/mesa.bbappend b/recipes-graphics/mesa/mesa.bbappend
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/recipes-graphics/mesa/mesa.bbappend
+++ b/recipes-graphics/mesa/mesa.bbappend
@@ -1 +1 @@
-PACKAGECONFIG:append:meson-gx = "lima panfrost"
+PACKAGECONFIG:append:meson-gx = " lima panfrost libclc"
